P.S. My cookies turned out EXACTLY like the photo - eg. they were not "flat" or "lacy". Perhaps other readers used margarine instead of butter? I was careful to not over grease the sheets and rinsed them with cold water between batches, a warm pan will also cause cookies to spread too much. I used refrigerated butter as opposed to room temperature (the mixer was able to break it down easily), which can also make a difference. Use eggs straight from the refrigerator to keep the mixture cool.

