I am a veteran cookie baker, and this has become one of my "Top 5 Hall of Fame" cookie recipes. My version, created partly from various reader comments, includes cutting out all the white sugar; using ordinary Baker's sweetened coconut and ordinary slivered almonds (conveniently eliminating all prep for the almonds except toasting in a nonstick skillet over medium heat); toasting the coconut and the oats together on a large rimmed cookie sheet in a 350-degree oven for 10 minutes, then allowing to cool before stirring into batter; and using Nestle Toll House chocolate chips. Forget the complicated two-cookie-sheet thing, just use one at a time and bake for 11 minutes. You will only need to do that twice. These huge, crunchy, not-too-sweet cookies always draw raves.

