I suggest when making any kind of cookie, that you combine the dry ingredients together (in this case, flour, baking powder and salt), and either wisk or sift them together and add to butter/sugar mixture in a few (3-4) smaller additions rather than all at once. This will save you from getting a chunk of baking powder in a bite of cookie, which to a baker, means certain death. By the way, these were a hit at work! I'll definately make them again.

