I tried a slightly drier mix and no nuts and definitely shorten cooking time and temp. Thus: [this is a one-half quantity recipe} 1 stick (1/2 cup) unsalted butter, softened 1/2 cup packed brown sugar ...Beat together butter and sugar in a bowl with an electric mixer at high speed until fluffy. ....add: 1 large egg ......and beat until just blended, ...... then add in.. 3/4 teaspoon vanilla 1/4 teaspoon baking soda 1/4 teaspoon salt. Add... 1/2 cup all-purpose flour ...and mix at low until blended. ..Stir in by hand: 1 1/4 cups old-fashioned oats* 1 cup packaged finely shredded unsweetened coconut 1 cup semi-sweet chocolate chips. Preheat oven to 350F. Arrange les than 1 Tbsp rounded portins, sing spoon and fingers, on 2 lightly buttered,large baking sheets (about 12 cookies per sheet) . Bake in upper and lower thirds of oven, switching position and rotating pans halfway through baking, until golden, about 9 minutes but check for burning on bottoms. Cool cookies on sheets 1 minute, then transfer with a spatula to racks to cool completely. Make more cookies in same manner. Makes about 24 cookies. *Experiment with 1 cup oats.

